{"id":14881863,"mediaExerciseId":"b6b1dddf-35c7-4e92-a953-eb8f682f61d4","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"24","chapterTitle":"Options and Corporate Finance","groupId":612498,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":822,"solutions":[{"id":5999939,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to understand options and stock risk.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define some terms.\n\n- **Put Option** is a contract that gives a holder the right but not the obligation to sell a stock.\n\n- **Call Option** is a contract that gives a holder the right to buy a stock.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"### If the risk of a stock increases, what is likely to happen to the price of call options on the stock.\n\nIf the risk of a stock increases, the price of call options on the stock will rise. When the stock price goes up, call options will increase in value because we will be able to buy the underlying asset at a lower price.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":98,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/012b425d77ea9e6c8cefdf7a18ba33dd/7a6689be28d17c485cc89f9e4f38685c/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/012b425d77ea9e6c8cefdf7a18ba33dd/7a6689be28d17c485cc89f9e4f38685c/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"### If the risk of a stock increases, what is likely to happen to the price of put options.\n\nIf the risk of a stock increases, the price of put options on the stock will fall. When the stock price goes up, put options will decrease in value because we will be only able to buy the underlying asset at a higher price.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/012b425d77ea9e6c8cefdf7a18ba33dd/bbfb914c36f891408f39740bd1686e1e/lateximg_large.png","width":753},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/012b425d77ea9e6c8cefdf7a18ba33dd/bbfb914c36f891408f39740bd1686e1e/lateximg.png","width":376}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"5652c622-cf25-466a-841a-e492cf59abed","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881864,"exerciseName":"7","page":822,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ca76c3d7-0f4a-433e-9f4c-8496973d3cfb","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-24-critical-thinking-questions-7-ca76c3d7-0f4a-433e-9f4c-8496973d3cfb"},{"id":14881865,"exerciseName":"8","page":822,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6464bb26-835a-4e46-a5fb-4697e75d2ad7","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-24-critical-thinkin